Yes, you can add the following CSS code to make the Call Now button white with Aegean colored text:

```
a.call-now-button {
  background-color: #FFFFFF;
  color: #00BFFF;
  padding: 10px 20px;
  border-radius: 5px;
  text-decoration: none;
  font-weight: bold;
}
```
And you can add the following CSS code to make the Chat Now button white with Aegean colored text:

```
a.chat-now-button {
  background-color: #FFFFFF;
  color: #00BFFF;
  padding: 10px 20px;
  border-radius: 5px;
  text-decoration: none;
  font-weight: bold;
}
```

To implement this, you can add the following HTML to your Google Sites website:

```
<a href="tel:123-456-7890" class="call-now-button">Call Now</a>

<a href="https://example.com/chat" class="chat-now-button">Chat Now</a>
```

Remember to replace https://example.com/chat with your valid chat link.

